This year’s Children’s Day was not the usual celebration for the kids who attended Tech and Fun Bootcamp which was an initiative of Kreateng Africa, a Software and Creative design company. The initiative which was designed to ‘catch them young’by training the kids to code and create graphic and motion design was held on the 27th & 28th of May, 2022. While speaking at the event, the CEO of Kreateng Africa, Adedayo Okunfolami pointed out that the bootcamp is in line with the commitment of Kreateng to empower kids with the knowledge of in demand tech skills in 2022. He further stated that tech skill bootcamp for kids to celebrate the annual children’s day is the best gift the organization can give as a contribution to the journey of the future champions. The bootcamp is targeted at kids within the age of 6 to 13 years to know the basics of tech and have fun at it had about 40 kids in attendance. Tutors who are top players in the tech industry, taught the kids the elementary parts of tech skills such as graphic designs, animation and coding. The tutors using simplified languageensured the kids were able to comprehend their teachings. The kids also played lots of games and had lots of goodies to take home. The high point of the event was when the kids had their practical session and got to demonstrate their learnings. One of the parents, Mrs Ademiju commended Kreateng Africa for coming up with what she described as a brilliant idea. She also wanted the kids to learn more about the skills.